What is this?
=============

This is the AlertEngine daemon, a part of Network Administration
Visualized.


What does it do?
================

The AlertEngine is responsible for monitoring the alert queue in NAV's
database, and dispatching alerts to user's according to the
subscriptions in their alert profiles.  It currently has the ability
to dispatch alerts via email, SMS and Jabber.

Much of the subscription profile interpretation logic can be found in
the profiles Django models, located in
subsystem/lib-python/nav/models/profiles.py.

Usage
=====

For more help on usage, run ``alertengine.py --help'' and see the
alertengine.conf config file.


Development
===========

All modules and functions are documented with pydoc, and the code is commented
where required.
